						<tr class="row"><td>1997</td><td>Academic Honors</td><td>In 1997, Torvalds received his master's degree (Laudatur Grade) from the Department of Computer Science at the University of Helsinki. Two years later he received honorary doctor status at Stockholm University, and in 2000, he received the same honor from his alma mater.</td></tr>
						<tr class="row"><td>1996</td><td>9793 Torvalds (Asteroid)</td><td>In 1996, the asteroid 9793 Torvalds was named after him.</td></tr>
						<tr class="row"><td>1995</td><td>Running Linux on AlphaStation</td><td>In the period 1994-1999 Torvalds developed versions of Linux on early AlphaServer systems made available to him by the engineering department of Digital Equipment Corporation. Compaq software engineers developed special Linux kernel modules. Linux distributions that ran on AlphaServer systems were Red Hat 7.2. and Gentoo Linux.</td></tr>
